India’s Bonds Gain as Cap on Foreign Investment May Be Raised

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-10-18T03:41:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/india-s-bonds-gain-as-cap-on-foreign-investment-may-be-raised.html
India ’s bonds gained a second day
after a finance ministry official said the nation may raise the
ceiling for foreign investment in sovereign debt.  The yield on the 7.8 percent note due April 2021 fell two
basis points to 8.74 percent as of 9:10 a.m. in Mumbai,
according to the central bank’s trading system.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
